{{update|date=February 2017}} {{Infobox sport tournament |year = 2009 |name = Denmark's Strongest Man |image = |location = varies, Denmark |establishment = 1983 |format = Multi-event competition |purse = |month_played = <!--Use if still played--> |current_champion = {{flagicon|Denmark}} Nikolai Hansen }}
'''Denmark's Strongest Man''' is an annual [[Strongman (strength athlete)|strongman]] contest held in various locations in [[Denmark]], and features exclusively Danish strength athletes.<ref name="davidhorne-gripmaster.com"/> The contest was first held in 1983 with [[Sven-Ole Thorsen]] winning the title.<ref name="davidhorne-gripmaster.com"/> [[Flemming Rasmussen (strongman)|Flemming Rasmussen]] holds 7 wins, and [[René Minkwitz]] holds 5 wins.<ref name="davidhorne-gripmaster.com"/>
