{{Infobox football biography | name = Fouad Rachid | image= | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1991|11|15|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Mayotte]] | height = | currentclub = [[CS Fola Esch|Fola Esch]] | clubnumber = 8 | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[AS Nancy|Nancy]] | years1 = 2010–2014 | clubs1 = Nancy B | caps1 = 56 | goals1 = 2 | years2 = 2010–2014 | clubs2 = [[AS Nancy|Nancy]] | caps2 = 8 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2011–2012 | clubs3 = → [[SAS Épinal|Épinal]] (loan) | caps3 = 11 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2015– | clubs4 = [[CS Fola Esch|Fola Esch]] | caps4 = 4 | goals4 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2011– | nationalteam1 = [[Comoros national football team|Comoros]] | nationalcaps1 = 3 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 6 June 2016 | ntupdate = 6 June 2016 }}
'''Fouad Rachid''' (born 15 November 1991) is a Comorian international [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Luxembourgish club [[CS Fola Esch|Fola Esch]] as a [[midfielder]].
==Career== Born in [[Mayotte]], Rachid made his debut for Nancy against [[SM Caen]] on 12 March 2011, coming on as a substitute for [[Julien Féret]] in a 2–0 win.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foot-national.com/55-5040-84-saison-football-Rachid-Fouad.html|title=Fouad Rachid sa saison en Ligue 1 2010/2011|publisher=FootNational|accessdate=2 February 2012}}</ref> He made his first senior start on 21 August 2011 as Nancy were beaten 1–2 at home by [[FC Sochaux-Montbéliard|Sochaux]]. On 22 December 2011, Rachid joined [[Championnat National]] side [[SAS Épinal|Épinal]] on [[loan (association football)|loan]] until the end of the 2011–12 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foot-national.com/foot-epinal-fouad-rachid-nancy-prete-30907.html|title=Epinal : Fouad Rachid (Nancy) prêté|publisher=FootNational|author=Erwann Penland|date=22 December 2011|accessdate=2 February 2012}}</ref>
===International career=== Rachid debuted with [[Comoros national football team|Comoros]] on November 11, 2011 in a 2014 FIFA World Cup qualifier match against [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]] played in [[Mitsamiouli]].<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/preliminaries/africa/matches/round=258330/match=300174498/index.html Debut with [[Comoros national football team|Comoros]] - FIFA report]</ref>
