{{Infobox football biography |name=Janiel Simon |image= |fullname=Janiel Simon |height={{height|ft=6|in=1}} |birth_date ={{Birth date and age|1981|6|11|df=yes}} |birth_place=[[Saint Mary Parish, Antigua and Barbuda|St Mary]], Antigua and Barbuda |currentclub= |clubnumber= |position=[[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] |youthyears1= 1999–2001 |youthclubs1= [[SAP FC|SAP]] |youthyears2= 2001–2002 |youthclubs2= [[Bryant & Stratton College|Bryant & Stratton Bobcats]] |youthyears3= 2003 |youthclubs3= [[South Carolina Upstate Spartans]] |youthyears4= 2007 |youthclubs4= [[Clayton State University|Clayton State Spartans]] |years1= 2004–2007 |clubs1= [[SAP FC|SAP]] |caps1= |goals1= |years2= 2008–2013 |clubs2= [[Empire FC|Empire]] |caps2= |goals2= |years3= 2013 |clubs3= [[Antigua Barracuda FC|Antigua Barracdua]] |caps3= 2 |goals3= 0 |nationalyears1=2000–2008 |nationalteam1=[[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] |nationalcaps1= 15 | nationalgoals1 = 0 |pcupdate=31 December 2008 |ntupdate=31 December 2008 }} '''Janiel Simon''' (born June 11, 1981) is an Antiguan [[association football|footballer]].
Janiel works for the Environmental division of the [[Antigua and Barbuda Government]]. He also was instrumental in organising a friendly match between a [[SAP F.C.]] side and a touring team of [[Explorer Scouts]] from the [[UK]]. The final score was: [[SAP F.C.]] 7- 5 [[Gladiator ESU football team]]. Janiel played most of the match, despite an eye injury, in defence rather than in goal.
He played 15 games for the [[University of South Carolina Upstate|Spartans]] in 2003 <ref>[http://upstatespartans.cstv.com/sports/m-soccer/stats/2003-2004/teamcume.html Overall Individual Statistics] - USC Spartanburg</ref> and 14 games for the [[Clayton State University|Lakers]] in 2007.<ref>[http://athletics.clayton.edu/msoc/2007/Stats/teamcume.htm Overall Individual Statistics] - Clayton State</ref>
==International career== Nicknamed ''Board'', Simon made his debut for [[Antigua and Barbuda national football team|Antigua and Barbuda]] in an April 2000 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Bermuda national football team|Bermuda]] and has earned over 20 caps since. He played in 8 [[FIFA World Cup qualification]] games.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=210321/index.html Record at FIFA Tournaments] - FIFA</ref>
