{{Infobox football biography |name = Mirlind Kryeziu |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Mirlind Kryeziu |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1997|1|26|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Zürich]], [[Switzerland]] |height = {{convert|1.98|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} |position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre-back]] |currentclub = [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] |clubnumber = 31 |youthyears1 = 2004–2015 |youthclubs1 = [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] |years1 = 2015– |clubs1 = [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] |caps1 = 18 |goals1 = 1 |years2 = 2015–2016 |clubs2 = → [[FC Biel-Bienne|Biel-Bienne]] (loan) |caps2 = 15 |goals2 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2013 |nationalteam1 = [[Switzerland national under-16 football team|Switzerland U16]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 1 |nationalyears2 = 2013–2014 |nationalteam2 = [[Switzerland national under-17 football team|Switzerland U17]] |nationalcaps2 = 11 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |nationalyears3 = 2015 |nationalteam3 = [[Switzerland national under-18 football team|Switzerland U18]] |nationalcaps3 = 2 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |nationalyears4 = 2015–2016 |nationalteam4 = [[Switzerland national under-19 football team|Switzerland U19]] |nationalcaps4 = 2 |nationalgoals4 = 0 |nationalyears5 = 2016–2017 |nationalteam5 = [[Switzerland national under-20 football team|Switzerland U20]] |nationalcaps5 = 2 |nationalgoals5 = 0 <!-- Don't add parameter unless he debuted with national team. |nationalyears6 = 2018– |nationalteam6 = [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] |nationalcaps6 = 0 |nationalgoals6 = 0 --> |club-update = 23 September 2018 |nationalteam-update = 9 November 2018 }} '''Mirlind Kryeziu''' (born 26 January 1997) is an Kosovo-Albanian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for Swiss club [[FC Zürich|Zürich]].
==Early life== Kryeziu was born in Zürich, Switzerland from Kosovo Albanian parents from Mleqani, a village near [[Mališevo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegrafi.com/ekskluzive-zvicra-e-donte-cdo-kusht-por-kryeziu-zgjodhi-vendlindjen-jam-lumtur-mezi-po-pres-te-luaj-per-kosoven/|title=Ekskluzive! Zvicra e donte me çdo kusht, por Kryeziu zgjodhi vendlindjen: Jam i lumtur, mezi po pres të luaj për Kosovën|trans-title=Exclusive! Switzerland loved it at all costs, but Kryeziu chose the birthplace: I'm happy, barely waiting to play for Kosovo|quote=Në një intervistë ekskluzive për Telegrafin, mbrojtësi nga Mleçani i Malishevës flet për prapaskenat dhe zgjedhjen e Kosovës|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|date=22 October 2018}}</ref> He holds [[Kosovan passport|Kosovan]] and [[Swiss passport|Swiss]] passports.
==Club career== ===Zürich=== In 2004, Kryeziu joined with youth academy of [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] at the age of 7.
====Loan at Biel-Bienne==== On 6 July 2015, Kryeziu joined [[Swiss Challenge League]] side [[FC Biel-Bienne|Biel-Bienne]], on a season-long loan. On 5 December 2015, he made his debut in a 1–0 away defeat against [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]] after being named in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/12/05/switzerland/challenge-league/fc-winterthur/fc-biel-bienne/2048070/|title=Winterthur (1–0) Biel-Bienne|website=Soccerway|date=5 December 2015}}</ref>
====Return to Zürich==== =====2016–17 season===== On 13 February 2017, Kryeziu made his debut in a 1–1 home draw against [[Neuchâtel Xamax FCS|Neuchâtel Xamax]] after being named in the starting line-up<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/02/13/switzerland/challenge-league/fc-zurich/neuchatel-xamax-fc/2243460/|title=Zürich (1–1) Neuchâtel Xamax|website=Soccerway|date=13 February 2017}}</ref> and helped the Zürich get promoted into the [[Swiss Super League]] that season. On 12 April 2017, he signed his first professional contract with [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] keeping him at the club until 2021.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fcz.ch/en/first-team/news/2017/mirlind-kryeziu-unterschreibt-ersten-profivertrag/|title=Mirlind Kryeziu signs first professional contract|publisher=[[FC Zürich]]|date=12 April 2017}}</ref>
=====2017–18 season===== On 31 March 2018, Kryeziu made his debut as a professional footballer in a 1–1 away draw against [[FC Sion|Sion]] after being named in the starting line-up.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2018/03/31/switzerland/super-league/fc-sion/fc-zurich/2467153/|title=Sion (1–1) Zürich|website=Soccerway|date=31 March 2018}}</ref>
==International career== <!------------------------------- ===Switzerland=== {{Empty section|date=March 2017}} ====Under-16==== {{Empty section|date=March 2017}} ====Under-17==== {{Empty section|date=March 2017}} ====Under-18==== {{Empty section|date=March 2017}} ====Under-19==== {{Empty section|date=March 2017}} ====Under-20==== {{Empty section|date=March 2017}} --------------------------------> ===Kosovo=== On 9 November 2018, Kryeziu received a call-up from [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] for the [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League D#Group 3|2018–19 UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Malta national football team|Malta]] and [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ffk-kosova.com/2018/11/09/challandes-publikon-listen-e-futbollisteve-per-dy-ndeshjet-e-radhes/|title=Challandes publikon listën e futbollistëve për dy ndeshjet e radhës|trans-title=Challandes publish the list of footballers for two next matches|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=9 November 2018}}</ref> he was an unused bench in these matches.
