{{National football association | Logo = Niger FF (logo).png | Founded = 1961 | FIFA affiliation = 1964 | Region = [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] | Region affiliation = 1965<ref>[[East African Standard]]. 20 November 1965.</ref> | President = Djibril Hima Hamidou | Coach = [[Harouna Doula Gabde]] | Website = http://www.fenifoot.ne }} The '''Nigerien Football Federation''' (FENIFOOT) ({{lang-fr|Fédération Nigerienne de Football}}) is the governing body of [[Football (soccer)|football]] in [[Niger]]. It organizes the national football league and the [[Niger national football team|national team]].
==History== The FENIFOOT was founded in 1961, and affiliated to [[FIFA]] in 1964 and to [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] in 1965.
