{{Infobox football biography | name= Philippe Durpes | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|3|6}} | birth_place = [[Capesterre-Belle-Eau|Capesterre]], [[Guadeloupe]], [[France]] | height = {{height|m=1.84|precision=0}} | currentclub = [[SO Romorantin]] | clubnumber = 17 | position = [[Defender (football)|Defender]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1995–1998 | years2 = 1998–2000 | years3 = 2000–2003 | years4 = 2003–present | clubs1 = [[RC Lens]] | clubs2 = [[Cercle Brugge]] | clubs3 = [[Amiens SC]] | clubs4 = [[SO Romorantin]] | caps1 = 3 | caps2 = 55 | caps3 = 14 | caps4 = 197 | goals1 = 0 | goals2 = 4 | goals3 = 1 | goals4 = 6 | nationalyears1 = 2007 | nationalteam1 = [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 07:09, 8 July 2009 (UTC) | ntupdate = 26 January 2009 }}
'''Philippe Durpes''' (born March 6, 1974 in [[Capesterre-Belle-Eau|Capesterre]]) is a football [[Defender (football)|defender]] from [[Guadeloupe]], [[France]].
He plays for French Championnat National club [[SO Romorantin]] and has represented the [[Guadeloupe national football team]] once, against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] in 2007.
