{{Infobox sport governing body |name = Royal Belgian Athletics League |abbrev = |logo = |logosize = |sport = [[Athletics (sport)|Athletics]] |category = |image = |caption = |jurisdiction = |founded = |aff = [[IAAF]] |affdate = |region = [[European Athletic Association|EAA]] |regionyear = |headquarters = [[Bruxelles]] |location = |president = Thomas Lefebvre and Eddy de Vogelaer |chairman = |chairperson = |chair = |chiefexec = |vicepresident = |secretary = Gery Follens |coach = |womenscoach = |key staff = |operating income = |sponsor = |year closed = |replaced = |prevfounded = |url = http://www.belgian-athletics.be/ |countryflag = Belgium |countryflag2 = |countryflag3 = |more = }}
The '''Royal Belgian Athletics League''' ([[Dutch language|Dutch]]: Koninklijke Belgische Atletiekbond, [[French language|French]]: ''Ligue Royale Belge d'Athlétisme'') is the governing body for the sport of athletics in [[Belgium]].
It consists of the Flemish League of Athletics (Dutch: Vlaamse Atletiekliga) and the Francophone League of Athletics (French: Ligue Belge Francophone d'Atléthisme), cooperating for organising the national championships and for participation in international competitions.
== Affiliations == *[[International Association of Athletics Federations]] (IAAF) *[[European Athletic Association]] (EAA) *[[Belgian Olympic and Interfederal Committee]]
== National records == The Federation maintains the [[Belgian records in athletics]].
