{{Infobox football club | clubname = San Pedro| image = | fullname = San Pedro Claver| nickname = | founded = | ground = [[Equatorial Guinea]] | capacity = | chairman = | mgrtitle = | manager = | league = | season = | position = | }} '''San Pedro Claver''', commonly known as '''San Pedro''', is an African [[Association football|football]] club based in [[Ebebiyín]], [[Equatorial Guinea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rsssf.com/tablese/eqguinea07.html|title=Equatorial Guinea 2007|website=rsssf.com|accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref><ref name="soccerway">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/teams/equatorial-guinea/san-pedro-claver/8309/|title=Equatorial Guinea - San Pedro Claver - Results, fixtures, squad, statistics, photos, videos and news - Soccerway|publisher=int.soccerway.com|accessdate=2014-06-15}}</ref>
The club is likely best known for their 2007 appearance in the CAF Confederation Cup, in which they lost to Benfica Luanda of Angola 7-1 on aggregate in the preliminary round.<ref name="soccerway"/>
San Pedro Claver withdrew from the 2008 championship and no record exists of their being active since.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rsssf.com/tablese/eqguinea08.html|title=Equatorial Guinea 2008|website=rsssf.com|accessdate=26 September 2018}}</ref>
