{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = ZELPO Aréna | image = [[File:Podbrezova.png|250px]] '''[[UEFA stadium categories|UEFA]]''' [[File:Nuvola apps mozilla.png|12px]][[File:Nuvola apps mozilla.png|12px]] | caption = | location = Kolkáreň 58, [[Podbrezová]], [[Slovakia]] | coordinates = {{coord|48|48|27.3|N|19|31|24.0|E|region:SK-BL_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | opened = 1959 | renovated = 2012, 2014–2015 | expanded = | closed = | owner = [[Železiarne Podbrezová]] | operator = [[FO ŽP Šport Podbrezová|ŽP Šport Podbrezová]] | surface = Grass | former_names = Stadium Kolkáreň | tenants = [[FO ŽP Šport Podbrezová|ŽP Šport Podbrezová]] | capacity = 4,061 | dimensions = 105 x 68 m | scoreboard = [[LED display|LED]] }}
'''ZELPO Aréna''' is a home [[football (soccer)|football]] [[stadium]] in [[Podbrezová]], [[Slovakia]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[FO ŽP Šport Podbrezová|ŽP Šport Podbrezová]]. The stadium holds 4,061 people. The intensity of the floodlighting is 1,200 lux.
